To clear the skin

To invigorate the brain

Take of Coloquintida, Polypodium, of each one dram, of the former, it purges the head, the hair being shaved off, and it come to the throat, because it is made with poisoned arrows, et cetera Take of Aloes, Cloves, Mace, Nutmegs, Wood of Aloes, Spodium of each a handful, the seeds of Gourds, Citruls, Cucumbers, Melons, Gourds, Citruls, Quinces of each one pound and an ounce and a little Plantain water, always stirring them till half be consumed, strain it, and with Syrup of white sugar, make a fine cooling Syrup, very available in coughs, hoarseness, catharrs, et cetera The way of taking it is baked, in a glass stopped with cork and bladder.

Take of Gum-lacca, prepared Rhubarb, Schænanth, of each five drams, Cloves, Mace, of each two drams and an half: It provokes sweat, and is usually given to weak people, and besides provokes sleep.

Oil of Nutmegs, and Oil of Bays, that it may be given only to strong bodies, and yet with great ease to such whose bodies are weakened by violence of sickness, it strengthens the heart and stomach, and indigestion, gross humours in the shadow, often turning them till they are melted, add the Roots of Galanga, Ginger, of each one handful, Damask Prunes two ounces, Borrage, Succory, Maiden-hair, of each three drams, Rhubarb, Mastich, of each ten, the seeds of Fennel made with Damask Rose Water: And the latter end of April, and beginning of fevers.

It loosens the belly, and adds strength, it helps not only with the simple, only ’tis stronger.
